===Alternative spellings===
*[[dood]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|do͞od}}, {{IPA|/duːd/}}, {{SAMPA|/du:d/}}
*: [[Rhymes:English:-uːd|Rhymes: -uːd]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# (Literal Meaning) An inexperienced cowboy
# {{slang}} A man.
# (''slang; used in the [[vocative]]'') A term of address for a man.
#: ''Relax, dude.''
# (''archaic'') A [[dandy]], a man who is very concerned about his dress and appearance.
# Slang for a cool person

====Synonyms====
*(''man''): [[bloke]] (''British, Australian, New Zealand slang (mainly in [[w:Southland|Southland]])''), [[chap]] (''British''), [[cove]] (''dated British''), [[guy]]
*(''term of address for a man''): [[mate]] (''British, Australian'')
*(''dandy''): [[dandy]], [[fop]], [[masher]]
*(''pimple''): Dudette(zit)

